      "content": "it's hard to believe it's just for \"personalized experience\" when it feels so much more calculated. like, why would it need to ping an unknown server exactly when my stress levels spike? it feels like they're reporting on me. what kind of telemetry data could a fridge actually be capable of collecting that would signal a person's emotional state to a server?",
